  h2 Humans respond to humans
  p Last week a friend asked me what my favourite blog is. I recommended Paul Modrowski’s blog, “On the Inside”. Later, it occurred to me that I’d never actually signed up to Paul’s email list.
  p All Paul had to do was ask and I’d have obliged. But instead, he relied on an impersonal email box. I feel like I owed it to Paul to subscribe. Evidently I didn’t feel like I owed his email email box.
  p On YouTube the majority of videos include some sort of!{' '}
    span.bold personal call-to-action
    |!{' '}— “Don’t forget to subscribe.” But for whatever reason the power of the human touch has yet to cross over to websites.
  p On observing this, I went through my old case studies adding a personal CTA to each one.
  img(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/eoi9.png" alt="Go viral with Hunter.io").img__70
  h2 Appearence matters
  p Everything up to now has been focused on perfecting structure. But it’s not going to count for much if your email box still looks like this:
  //- p Ok, enough structure. It’s not going to count for much much if your email box still looks like this:
  img(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/eoi7.png" alt="Go viral with Hunter.io").img__60
  p I've got 3 simple rules to improve any email section:
  p.list.list__top 1) Explain!{' '}
    span.bold why
    |!{' '}people should sign up
  p.list 2) Add social proof (e.g. No. of subscribers, unsubscribe rate, quote)
  p.list.list__bottom 3) Replace “Subscribe” with a value-based CTA
  img(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/eoi8.png" alt="Go viral with Hunter.io").img__90
  //- video(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/eoi.mp4" class="img__85" playsinline="playsinline" controls="controls")
  h2 Summary
  p Choosing whether or not to subscribe to an email list is a split-second decision. This means that subtle psychological tweaks can make a big difference.
  p Here’s the checklist:
  p.list.list__top 1) 100% CTA coverage
  p.list 2) Exit-intent popup
  p.list 3) Subscribe page
  p.list 4) Ask as a human
  p.list 5) Give a clear reason to sign up
  p.list 6) Social Proof
  p.list 7) Value-based messaging
  p And now, young Padawan, as you walk through the valley of the shadow of death you shall fear no evil.
  h2 *Popup Implementation
  p Exit-intent popup implementation is easier than you think. With code it looks like:
  img(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/eoi4.png" alt="Exit itent popup code").img__80
  p And without code:
  p.list.list__top 1) OptinMonster connects with Email Octopus
  p.list.list__bottom 2) MailerMunch & Wisepops connects with Mailchimp, Klaviyo etc ...
  p It's worth pointing out that most exit-intent popups default to timeout based on mobile.
